write_spd(25.10)                                              write_spd(25.10)

Name
       write_spd  - Dumps the SPD file based on the user-selected signals with
       corresponding shielding and PG shapes directly

Syntax
       write_spd

       [-help]

       -file <spdFileName>

       [{-nets  <netName(s)>   |   -selected   }   [-cut_margin   <cutMargin>]
       [-with_shield ]]

       Dumps  the SPD file based on the user-selected signals with correspond-
       ing shielding and PG shapes directly.

       The write_spd command provides the efficiency of the  Signal  Integrity
       (SI) flow integration between Integrity 3D-IC and Sigrity as it:

              * Allows  Innovus  to  directly  generate  the SPD file based on
                user-selected signals, along with the corresponding  shielding
                and Power/Ground (PG) shapes. This eliminates the need for the
                GDS2SPD  flow, which requires a stream-out as a preceding step
                and takes considerable runtime.

              * Provides options to define the region for SPD generation based
                on the selected nets. Users can specify a margin to expand the
                region, ensuring that all relevant signals and their shielding
                are included.

              * Ensures that the shielding for the selected  signals  is  pre-
                served.  Additionally,  it  maintains  the  PG nets within the
                specified margin, which is important for SI extraction and re-
                turn path considerations.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each write_spd parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_spd

       -cut_margin <cutMargin>
              Specifies the cut margin expanded from the specified nets bound-
              ing  box.  The -cut_margin option must be used with the -nets or
              -selected options.

       -file <spdFileName>
              Specifies the SPD file name.

       -nets <netName(s)>
              Specifies named nets. If you specify one net name,  you  do  not
              need the braces around the name.

       -selected
              Specifies  the  selected nets. You can select nets using the se-
              lect_obj command.

              If  you  do  not  specify  the  -nets  or  -selected  parameter,
              write_spd generates the SPD file from the whole design.

       -with_shield
              By  default,  write_spd  does  not  consider the completeness of
              shielding when the SPD file is generated for the selected nets.

              When specified, the -with_shield option ensures that the shield-
              ing for corresponding selected signals is considered  during  SI
              analysis to prevent cross-talk. It generates the shielding rout-
              ing  (if  any)  of  the specified nets. This option must be used
              with the -nets or -selected option.

       Related Information

